    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The request here is a bit different to our current behaviour.  Our regular move will have units fire on any existing target, but not aquire anything new.  Our attack-move will have the units stop or pursue their targets.  @deniz1a wants something in between: turreted units that acquire and fire on anything in range without affecting their movement (basically the current move behaviour, but with active scanning for new targets).  I think this is a reasonable request for our AttackAnything stance, but the other modes should behave as they do now.\n"
